The history of a brand:
IBM, the innovator, enters its second century
If someone were to look for the word that best expresses IBM strategy, the closest one would be "long term".
For a broad public IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has passed a hundred years.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first head, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left behind the slogan that many of the world's problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
Its slogan "THINK!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant would develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
It was the basis of the corporate care culture developed by Watson.
For us IBM means long-term thinking of continuous movements towards the future.
IBM has survived a hundred years because it has always remained true to its core values and yet has not been afraid to change everyone else around it.
It has allowed us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will achieve even more", said the firm's current director, Samuel J. Palmisano, on the occasion of the anniversary.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to care for his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacation, employer-paid insurance plus a stylish employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and commercials.
Similarly, IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The company was originally great at talent discovery - as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who is expected to replace Palmisano as head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for thirty years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has been doing what's called jamy, online brainstorming, which has led to many future strategies and innovations.
It's no wonder he has a lot of ideas - the firm has almost 500,000 people working.
An Institution with a Good Name
It is the internal and external image of the company that ensures its secure position in the business world.
"From the beginning IBM was more of an institution than a technology firm", said Rosabeth Moss Kanter, professor of economics at Harvard Business School and author of the book on IBM.
"IBM is not a technology firm but a firm that helps solve business problems using its technology", added Geogre Colony of consulting firm Forrester Research.
As the firm itself says there is a difference between entering the market and creating that market.
IBM - or the "Big Blue", as it is known in the United States because of its slogan - in a hundred years it has grown into one of the largest companies in the world.
It is obviously the most versatile technology firm - it develops software, hardware, infrastructure, hosting, consulting services from server products to nanotechnology.
It has many of the patents of all American technology firms and five of its employees have received a Nobel Prize.
Among his discoveries are the cash machine, the credit card, the financial swap, the barcode, and the floppy disk.
IBM has this year, with $220 billion, become the second largest technology firm by market capitalization (first is Apple), when it first overtook Microsoft in 1996.
