It is not so much a book about what happened, he says, but a "book describing what it might have been like", containing "feelings, impressions, experiences and moods".
"Beauty and Sorrow" summarizes the wartime experiences of 20 ordinary men and women on both sides of the conflict, from young school girls and botanists to rock climbers, doctors, paramedics and salesmen.
Some of them will become heroes.
