But on the same day the bill failed, the House of Representatives also rejected a measure to reduce funding for US operations in Libya.
The US mission thus remained in a form of legislative purgatory - Congress sufficiently upset to criticize Obama's management of the mission, but not enough to cut the grass under his feet.
