Less liquidity
Unemployment in Sinaloa during the year is multifactorial, according to economist Gerardo L√≥pez Cervantes, director of the Faculty of Economic and Social Sciences at the UAS, the rise in unemployment can be explained indirectly by actions taken by public policy.
