By 2017, the structural public deficit must decrease by 0.75% of GDP each year and, from 2017, the federal government's structural public deficit must not exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while the regional states and municipalities must present balanced budgets.
The objective is to bring public debt below the 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Treaty by 2020/21.
